description.narrative:
It is an expert service for increased trade / gender equality, poverty reduction that is to be seconded to World Bank Trade and Competitiveness Global Practice; which works to promote economic growth, poverty reduction, job creation and to promote increased incomes in poor countries in order to eradicate poverty and promote greater prosperity.
The effort is part of the central secondment program for multilateral for middle and senior level. This follows the DG decision from 2013-02-08 and the decision on the Revised Objective for the program from 2016-06-16. The motive and purpose of the program are;
- Seconding in a competence supply perspective The seconding policies of international systems are based on a high degree of reciprocity. They are there in addition to the regular recruitment systems, to enable more targeted and time-limited supply of skills, usually in areas where there is a mutual interest between the country that secondizes and the organization that receives.
